    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9d221d3cbadc78b75ae7027fbf8ce0f0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 96506,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 262282,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/262282/geekzspot",
                "reputation": 873,
                "display_name": "geekzspot"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1340348664,
            "creation_date": 1267593296,
            "body": "<p>The default standard output device in the Oracle Java virtual machine (JVM) is the current trace file.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you want to reroute all standard output from a program executing in the server--output from any <code>System.out.println()<\/code> calls, for example--to a user screen, you can execute the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/cd/E11882_01/java.112/e10588/appendixa.htm#autoId8\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">SET_OUTPUT()<\/a> procedure of the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/cd/E11882_01/java.112/e10588/appendixa.htm#JJDEV13000\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">DBMS_JAVA<\/a> package as in the following example. <\/p>\n\n<p>Input the buffer size in bytes (10,000 bytes in this case).<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>sqlplus&gt; execute dbms_java.set_output(10000);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Output exceeding the buffer size will be lost.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you want your code executing in the server to expressly output to the user screen, you can also use the PL-SQL <strong>DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE()<\/strong> <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/cd/E11882_01/appdev.112/e25788/d_output.htm#ARPLS67327\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">3<\/a> procedure instead of the Java <code>System.out.println()<\/code> method.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 2368928,
            "question_id": 2183103,
            "last_edit_date": 1340348664
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/09939a1d3bd9c1af199a948bdc68cb71?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
