            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1265105486,
            "creation_date": 1265105486,
            "body": "<p>SQL Developer has a built-in PL/SQL debugger.  There is a useful guide on how to use it <a href=\"http://www.oracle.com/technology/obe/sqldev_obe/plsql_debug/plsql_debug.htm#t5\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" title=\"Developing and Debugging PL/SQL using Oracle SQL Developer\">here<\/a>.  Pay special attention to the need for DEBUG CONNECT SESSION and DEBUG ANY PROCEDURE privileges.<\/p>\n\n<p>I admit I don't know whether this works for SQLJ but it seems like the best place to start.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 2183203,
